Package com.BrethrenAce.GameEngine

Class Move

java.lang.Object
com.BrethrenAce.GameEngine.Move
public class Move
extends java.lang.Object
A class that decides the mobility of all pieces and has several functions, mainly to check current game scenario(e.g. winning). All pieces movement are the same, i.e. a step forwards, backwards and sidewards. Also, Move class evaluates all the four possible moves and categorized them as one of the following, "attacking", "draw", "normal", and "invalid." Finally, Move class checks to see if the executing move will conclude the game and declase the winner. Author: Brethren de la Gente Date: 2021-01-07

  • Method Details

    • evaluateMove

      public void evaluateMove()
      Evaluates the move for this Move instance based on the target tile location and the source piece to be moved. "attacking" = if target Tile contains opposing piece Alliance. "normal" = if target Tile is empty. "invalid" = if target Tile contains friendly piece Alliance. "draw" = if target Tile contains opposing piece Alliance and has the same rank, with the exception of Flag rank.
